Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addFillerGap(25.10)                                        addFillerGap(25.10)

Name
       addFillerGap  -  Moves placed standard cell instances to create gaps so
       that filler cells can be added

Syntax
       addFillerGap

       <minGap >

       [-effort {none | low | medium | high}]

       [-radius <micron>]

       Moves placed standard cell instances to  create  gaps  so  that  filler
       cells  can  be added. Tries to move cells to create a gap of the speci-
       fied size. If enough space is not available,  moves  cells  until  they
       touch  each  other.  If a gap already exists, and it is larger than the
       specified size, the command does not move cells to make it smaller.

       By default, this command deletes all routing, because the routing is no
       longer valid due to the movement of the cells. To override this  behav-
       ior, specify the following command:

       setPlaceMode -place_detail_preserve_routing true

       This command has the following limitations:

              * It does not moved FIXED cells.

              * It does not guarantee to that all gaps will be larger than the
                specified minimum gap size.

       Use this command after placement and before routing.

Parameters
       <minGap>
              Specifies  the  minimum-size  gap  in which a filler cell can be
              added. Unit is micron.

       -effort {none | low| medium | high}
              Specifies the effort the command needs to spend for honoring the
              given gap constraint.

              * none effort specifies that no standard cell is moved for  hon-
                oring the giving gap constraint.

              * low  effort  specifies  that only single height standard cells
                can be moved within the same row.

              * medium effort specifies that only single height standard cells
                can be moved across the rows.

              * high effort specifies that the standard  cells  can  be  moved
                across  rows,  and  double  height standard cells can be moved
                within the same row.

              Default: low

       -radius <micron>
              Specifies the searching radius when solving the  minimum  filler
              gap.

              Default: 16

Example
       The  following command moves standard cells within a row to create gaps
       of at least two microns between the cells:

       addFillerGap 0.168

Related Information
              * setPlaceMode

